   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "Compliance appears in the model as a static haircut inside serviceableFactor — a level, not a schedule. Because the funnel has no time axis, a delay risk masquerades as an already-priced reach discount, and 'conservative ramp' in the profile reads as if it already absorbs slippage.",
 "falsifier": "A complete, dated compliance dossier (CE declaration, RoHS/WEEE registrations incl. stiftung EAR number, EORI) plus at least one distributor or operator listing in hand before the Year-1 clock starts.",
 "likelihoodRationale": "First-time EU market entry for networked electrical hardware routinely takes 2–4 quarters across test-lab lead times and national registrations; the venture is pre-launch with no evidence in the ledger that any of these artifacts exist yet. [evidence revision: Evidence confirms the gates exist and are serialized and precede commercial presence, supporting the mechanism's direction. But the load-bearing quantum — a full two-quarter slip — is undercut for a non-wireless PDU where CE (EMC+LVD, no Notified Body/RED) fits inside 2-12 weeks. WEEE authorized-rep appointment, EORI, and first-listing pull-through still consume meaningful serialized time, so a material (roughly one-quarter+) front-end erosion remains plausible for a pre-launch venture with no artifacts. Net slightly below prior 0.55.]"
